title: For Sale:  German Made JANA BISON 22 Single Action Hvy Barrel Revolver GR8 Boat/Tacklebox/Camp/Truck/Boat Gun
postcontent: This is a low cost but darn nicely made single action. The frame was painted and is not so pretty as theres lines and swirls and whatever else, but the frame is very small pieces on these. The barrel is nicely blued and a heavy one. The cylinder is also blued with just some wear on the edge and a drag line. It shoots with ZERO muzzle movement. It feels like shooting an airgun as all that weight up front just holds it steady. It weighs just under 2 pounds so more than most poly pistols as its all steel. Plastic grips in white and loads through a side gate so you dont have to remove the cylinder like the old H&R and Iver Johnson 22s that were sold as camp/truck/tacklebox guns. The barrel is pinned in like the better ones and the cylinder has recessed chambers so the rounds fit flush. Theres some proof marks all over and on the receiver is a shield with 67 inside which MAY be the year. I find 7 marks without taking the grips off. I fired it one time only as I got it in a group deal and did not target test it. Just had fun testing it out to be sure it works. Locks up real tight when you pull the trigger and there are 3 hammer positions. Half-cock lets the cylinder turn for loading/unloading. Says GERMANY on the barrel, but strangely, not West Germany. Something different and cool, as you will not run into any other JANA revolvers. Not a collector for sure, but if you are going to have a camp/boat/fishing gun whether to finish a gator, snag dinner while camping or just-in-case...might as well have something interesting. Im pretty sure it is 1967 as it predates the GCA of 1968 which required import stamps. Also a great beginner gun to teach the basics of sights, safety and shooting. You wont mind a ding or scratch and if it does get some, the value stays the same. MANY PHOTOS AVAILABLE
